# 7. 同じ気持ち

An: My dad used to be a musician in this town.
Shiho: Oh... Yeah, I've heard. He's famous, right?
An: Yes, exactly! And about three years ago, he put on this event called RAD WEEKEND with fellow musicians in this town.
Shiho: That's that event that's supposed to have been legendary...
An: Yeah. It really was electric. It was as if everyone in the venue came together with the same energy, like no one could help but sing and shout along.
An: Ever since that event, I've dreamed of surpassing it... And that's what me and my teammates are working toward.
An: Recently, we even started getting together with other musicians to hold our own events. Just the other day we pulled off an amazing one!
An: They're all really good at what they do. Akito relentlessly pushes us to keep getting better... Toya is an incredible songwriter...
An: And Kohane... Ever since we met, I've been proud to be her partner! Her singing always gets me pumped.
Shiho: Now that you mention it, I was surprised when I saw her sing at Shibuya Festa. She seemed so different from her usual self.
An: It's not like she's already been singing for years, so it's crazy, right? She's growing too fast for me to even stop and admire her.
An: Kohane's honestly...too incredible. At our last event, she...
An: The point is, I need to get my head in the game!
An: So, I got a little frenzied. I've been using any spare time I have to practice like today.
An: I want to surpass RAD WEEKEND no matter what it takes. But I'm not chasing that dream alone anymore.
An: I want to realize that dream with Kohane—with all of them—singing by my side.
Shiho: (Frenzied...)
Shiho: (Even with as much singing talent as she has, Shiraishi still thinks like that.)
Shiho: (Shiraishi's driven by such a powerful, intense feeling...)
Shiho: (It's driving her to give the best performance she can with the people closest to her...)
Saki: By the time the day of our show rolls around, we'll be standing shoulder-to-shoulder with you...!
Saki: Then, we can run across the finish line hand in hand, like that race we did way back when!
An: I want to realize that dream with Kohane—with all of them—singing by my side.
Shiho: (I feel just the same as her.)
Shiho: I...understand. I know what it's like to chase a dream with the people you love.
Shiho: In my case, I want to go pro with the others.
An: Hinomori...
Shiho: I have friends who are determined to follow me and keep making music together. I'm able to keep trying thanks to them.
Shiho: Because I have them, I think I'm... We're closer to our dream of going pro.
Shiho: Their passion and their music keep me going.
Shiho: And the same goes for you, Shiraishi... I think the way you're feeling is important.
Shiho: I'm sure your feelings will become a kind of fuel to take your team higher.
An: My...feelings will...?
Shiho: Yes. I think so.
An: ... I hope you're right.
Shiho: Hey, Shiraishi. Do you wanna hear a song that we'll be playing at our solo show?
An: Huh? Where did that come from so suddenly?
Shiho: The way you sang earlier really resonated with me. And I don't like not paying people back.
An: What? That's a weird reason.
An: But, okay then. I'd like to hear it.
Shiho: (I'll play Saki's song. I always make sure to have the backing track we made for practice.)
Shiho: (As long as I have this, even when I practice by myself, I'm never alone. The others are there to take my performance higher.)
Shiho: (Looks like my amp's good as new.)
Shiho: Okay, I'll get started then.
An: (Hinomori's putting such intense emotion into this. She's playing with so much definition and clarity... She's so good.)
An: (She takes music seriously. She's passionate enough to confidently devote her life to this. And she doesn't hesitate for a second.)
An: (Hinomori's so cool.)
Shiho: *Sigh*
An: Thank you, Hinomori. I'm feeling kinda energized after that!
Shiho: Really? That's great.
An: Hey, would you be interested in performing one more song, together this time?
Shiho: Huh? Together... Like a session?
An: Yeah! It's only natural to want to perform with someone so cool! What do you say?
Shiho: Nice. I've been wanting to perform with you too, so I'm down.
An: Really?! Yay!
Shiho: In that case, how about this song...
